Health officials in Geneva are considering developing a vaccine for the deadly H5N1 bird flu strain that has caused global concern.
In Hong Kong, a three-year-old boy and a man died from the virus, with a 13-year-old girl currently hospitalized.
Authorities are urging caution, inspecting poultry farms, and advising residents to buy from licensed vendors.
Macao is also on alert, emphasizing hygiene and proper cooking practices.
Despite increased monitoring, imported poultry is deemed safe.
The World Health Organization and US experts are assisting in the investigation, with no evidence of human-to-human transmission reported.
